Anti-government protesters destroy a Chinese flag during a rally in a shopping mall in Sha Tin, Hong Kong, China September 22, 2019.  JOHANNESBURG - Protests have continued for another day in Hong Kong. Several hundred demonstrators have gathered in a mall where they trampled and set fire to the Chinese national flag. READ: Hong Kong protesters appeal to Trump for help China will be celebrating its 70th anniversary next month. Hong Kong joined China in 1997 in an agreement made with the British government.